Package indexing

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IIndexer
    Defines the methods an Indexer needs to implement.
    ITokenStream<T>
    Defines the methods a TokenStream needs to implement.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockIndexer
    Class to perform SPIMI indexing of a set of files ( #indexFiles(File[], File, boolean)) or a single zipped file ( #indexZipFile(File, File, boolean)).
    BufferedArffMatrixReader
    Class to read a gzipped ARFF file
    BufferedArffMatrixWriter
    Class that provides fast buffered writing of block matrices while trying to allocate as little memory as possible.
    BufferedBlockDictionaryReader
    Class to read arbitrarily sized BlockDictionaries one chunk of BUFFER_SIZE_IN_BYTES at a time.
    BufferedBlockDictionaryWriter
    Class that provides fast buffered writing of block dictionaries while trying to allocate as little memory as possible.
    BufferedBlockMatrixReader
    Class to read arbitrarily sized BlockDictionaries one chunk of BUFFER_SIZE_IN_BYTES at a time.
    BufferedBlockMatrixWriter
    Class that provides fast buffered writing of block matrices while trying to allocate as little memory as possible.
    PriorityQueueTermReaderComparator<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Comparator to sort our priority queue first by the term and then by the number of the reader (= fileNumber).
    PriorityQueueTermReaderToken<T>
    Helper DAO that simply stores a tuple.
    Stemmer
    Stemmer, implementing the Porter Stemming Algorithm The Stemmer class transforms a word into its root form.
    ZipTokenStream
    Class to tokenize a zipped file using standard Java API's zipFile functionality.
